00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:52,230
Maybe it’s because of the yellow sand,

17
00:01:52,960 --> 00:01:55,400
the sky of Yanbei is never clear

18
00:01:55,890 --> 00:01:57,370
even when it’s sunny.

19
00:01:58,390 --> 00:02:00,500
I like the rain here.

20
00:02:01,450 --> 00:02:03,110
It’s less dense than that in Wei,

21
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:05,320
but fresh and cool.

22
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:08,540
I wish there’d be more rain.

23
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:10,180
By the way,

24
00:02:10,570 --> 00:02:11,990
how are Mr. Chen and the others?

25
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:13,270
Young Master,

26
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:14,730
they’ve been escorted

27
00:02:14,730 --> 00:02:16,190
to a safe place.

28
00:02:16,740 --> 00:02:18,160
According to him,

29
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:19,810
the one who released them wore a mask.

30
00:02:20,250 --> 00:02:22,180
It seemed to be a man.

31
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:23,750
That person is familiar

32
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:24,580
with Hongchuan.

33
00:02:24,990 --> 00:02:26,160
Who would that be?

34
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:31,840
A message came from Chang’an.

35
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:33,020
His Majesty is too sick

36
00:02:33,020 --> 00:02:34,500
to control the court.

37
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:36,160
Now, Prince Che

38
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:38,030
is taking charge of everything.

39
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:39,850
In that case,

40
00:02:40,010 --> 00:02:41,830
peace might be restored

41
00:02:41,830 --> 00:02:42,650
sooner.

42
00:02:42,650 --> 00:02:43,850
He who is unjust

43
00:02:43,850 --> 00:02:44,970
is doomed to destruction.

44
00:02:44,970 --> 00:02:46,360
Am I right, Your Highness?

45
00:02:47,190 --> 00:02:50,060
I have sworn long ago
to paint Chang’an with blood,

46
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,240
and cut off that man’s head

47
00:02:53,620 --> 00:02:55,390
to avenge the murder of our warriors.

48
00:02:56,100 --> 00:02:57,330
How can he die

49
00:02:57,330 --> 00:02:58,400
so easily?

50
00:02:58,710 --> 00:03:00,300
I agree, Your Highness.

51
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:02,080
He must be killed by us

52
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:03,490
so that those who died for Yanbei

53
00:03:03,490 --> 00:03:04,950
can rest in peace.

54
00:03:05,220 --> 00:03:07,130
That geezer is doomed.

55
00:03:07,130 --> 00:03:08,670
But his successor will still

56
00:03:08,670 --> 00:03:10,030
be our biggest threat.

57
00:03:10,170 --> 00:03:12,080
Prince Che is prudent.

58
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:13,360
He can see the big picture.

59
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:16,370
It’s too soon to call him a threat.

60
00:03:16,830 --> 00:03:18,290
Sounds like

61
00:03:19,450 --> 00:03:21,870
you and he

62
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:23,210
go way back, Zhong Yu.

63
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:25,930
Cheng Yuan, what are you insinuating?

64
00:03:26,340 --> 00:03:27,770
If you are not

65
00:03:27,770 --> 00:03:28,590
close friends,

66
00:03:28,590 --> 00:03:29,600
how do you know

67
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:30,650
he is not a threat?

68
00:03:31,940 --> 00:03:32,750
Cheng Yuan.

69
00:03:34,170 --> 00:03:35,510
No matter who ascends the throne,

70
00:03:36,070 --> 00:03:38,270
this war is inevitable.

71
00:03:39,810 --> 00:03:40,860
Pass my order.

72
00:03:41,950 --> 00:03:44,510
Prepare enough troops
and supplies quickly.

73
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:46,050
Yes.

74
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:48,150
Your Highness, please think twice.

75
00:03:48,750 --> 00:03:49,820
If the war is on again,

76
00:03:50,170 --> 00:03:51,580
countless families

77
00:03:51,580 --> 00:03:52,570
will be ruined.

78
00:03:52,940 --> 00:03:54,230
Stability has just been restored.

79
00:03:54,610 --> 00:03:56,050
We can’t afford another war.

80
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:57,990
I’ve said it long ago

81
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,760
that women should never

82
00:03:59,760 --> 00:04:01,310
lead the army to battle.

83
00:04:01,790 --> 00:04:02,750
Yanbei and Wei

84
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:04,270
are mortal enemies.

85
00:04:04,500 --> 00:04:06,360
If we back off,

86
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,520
they’ll take every corner of our land

87
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:09,440
sooner or later.

88
00:04:12,660 --> 00:04:14,720
You know the best

89
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:16,730
how it feels to be whipped by a woman.

90
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,290
General Cheng.

91
00:04:22,370 --> 00:04:25,070
Don’t cross the line.

92
00:04:25,310 --> 00:04:26,330
Did I?

93
00:04:26,930 --> 00:04:28,550
As a general,

94
00:04:28,550 --> 00:04:30,170
you should know well about

95
00:04:30,170 --> 00:04:31,730
the current situation.

96
00:04:32,110 --> 00:04:33,660
We have strong enemies outside

97
00:04:33,660 --> 00:04:34,760
and traitors among us.

98
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:36,310
Today, someone

99
00:04:36,310 --> 00:04:37,980
let those spies from Wei go.

100
00:04:37,980 --> 00:04:39,550
Then tomorrow that person

101
00:04:39,550 --> 00:04:40,840
is likely to assassinate His Highness.

102
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:42,860
What do you mean?

103
00:04:44,930 --> 00:04:45,910
Your Highness.

104
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:50,350
Those who attempted
to burn the barn escaped.

105
00:04:50,610 --> 00:04:52,000
But the strange thing is

106
00:04:52,220 --> 00:04:54,120
none of the shackles in prison

107
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:56,200
were damaged by force.

108
00:04:56,470 --> 00:04:57,900
So someone must have used keys

109
00:04:57,900 --> 00:04:58,860
to free them.

110
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:00,980
I think that traitor

111
00:05:00,980 --> 00:05:02,190
is one of us.

112
00:05:03,220 --> 00:05:04,660
